1926;;The Strong Man;;American;;Frank Capra;;Harry Langdon, Priscilla Bonner, Gertrude Astor;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Strong_Man;;Paul Bergot (Harry Langdon) is a Belgian immigrant to the United States who has fallen in love with Mary Brown (Priscilla Bonner), a blind woman. They met as pen-pals when he was fighting in Europe during World War I. Mary even sent Paul a photo of her.<br><br>Paul searches for Mary Brown by asking every woman he meets if she is Mary Brown. By accident he rescues her town from crooks and bootleggers.